# üöÄ Ultimate JavaScript Comprehensive Guide

## 1. Fundamentals

### 1.1 Variables

```javascript
// Variable Declarations
let dynamicVar = "Changeable"; // Block-scoped, can be reassigned
const constantVar = "Fixed"; // Block-scoped, cannot be reassigned
var globalVar = "Old Style"; // Function-scoped (avoid in modern JS)
```

### 1.2 Data Types

- **Primitive Types**

  - String: Text data
  - Number: Numeric values
  - Boolean: true/false
  - Undefined: Unassigned value
  - Null: Intentional absence of value
  - Symbol: Unique identifier
  - BigInt: Large integer values

- **Reference Types**
  - Object
  - Array
  - Function

## 2. Operators

### 2.1 Arithmetic Operators

```javascript
let addition = 5 + 3; // 8
let subtraction = 10 - 4; // 6
let multiplication = 3 * 4; // 12
let division = 15 / 3; // 5
let modulus = 10 % 3; // 1
let exponentiation = 2 ** 3; // 8
```

### 2.2 Comparison Operators

```javascript
let equal = 5 == "5"; // Loose equality: true
let strictEqual = 5 === "5"; // Strict equality: false
let notEqual = 5 != "5"; // Loose inequality: false
let strictNotEqual = 5 !== "5"; // Strict inequality: true
```

### 2.3 Logical Operators

```javascript
let andOperator = true && false; // Logical AND
let orOperator = true || false; // Logical OR
let notOperator = !true; // Logical NOT
```

## 3. Control Structures

### 3.1 Conditional Statements

```javascript
if (condition) {
  // Code when true
} else if (anotherCondition) {
  // Alternative condition
} else {
  // Default case
}

switch (variable) {
  case value1:
    // Code for value1
    break;
  default:
  // Default code
}
```

### 3.2 Loops

```javascript
// For Loop
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  // Repeated code
}

// While Loop
while (condition) {
  // Repeated code
}

// Do-While Loop
do {
  // Code executed at least once
} while (condition);

// For...of (iterate over values)
for (let item of array) {
  // Code for each item
}

// For...in (iterate over object keys)
for (let key in object) {
  // Code for each key
}
```

## 4. Functions

### 4.1 Function Types

```javascript
// Function Declaration
function standardFunction(param1, param2) {
  return result;
}

// Arrow Function
const arrowFunction = (param) => {
  return result;
};

// Anonymous Function
const anonymousFunc = function () {
  // Function body
};

// Immediately Invoked Function Expression (IIFE)
(function () {
  // Immediate execution
})();
```

## 5. Arrays

### 5.1 Array Methods

```javascript
let fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"];
fruits.push("date"); // Add to end
fruits.pop(); // Remove from end
fruits.map((fruit) => fruit.toUpperCase()); // Transform
fruits.filter((fruit) => fruit.length > 5); // Filter
fruits.reduce((acc, curr) => acc + curr); // Reduce
```

## 6. Objects

### 6.1 Object Methods

```javascript
const person = { name: "John", age: 30 };
Object.keys(person); // Get keys
Object.values(person); // Get values
Object.entries(person); // Get key-value pairs
Object.assign({}, person); // Clone object
```

## 7. Asynchronous Programming

### 7.1 Promises

```javascript
async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(url);
    const data = await response.json();
    return data;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error);
  }
}
```

## 8. ES6+ Features

### 8.1 Destructuring

```javascript
const { prop1, prop2 } = object;
const [first, second] = array;
```

### 8.2 Spread & Rest Operators

```javascript
const newArray = [...oldArray]; // Spread
function func(...args) {} // Rest
```

## 9. Classes

### 9.1 Class Syntax

```javascript
class MyClass {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }

  method() {
    console.log(this.name);
  }

  static staticMethod() {
    // Class method
  }
}
```

## 10. Error Handling

### 10.1 Try-Catch

```javascript
try {
  // Potential error code
} catch (error) {
  console.error("An error occurred:", error);
} finally {
  // Always executes
}
```

## 11. DOM Manipulation

### 11.1 Selecting Elements

```javascript
document.getElementById("elementId");
document.querySelector(".className");
document.querySelectorAll("selector");
```

### 11.2 Creating & Modifying Elements

```javascript
const newElement = document.createElement("div");
element.appendChild(newElement);
element.textContent = "New Text";
```

### 11.3 Event Handling

```javascript
element.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
  // Event handling logic
});
```

## 12. Modules

### 12.1 Import/Export

```javascript
export const myVariable = "exported";
import { myVariable } from "./module.js";
```

## Conclusion

This guide covers the fundamental and advanced concepts of JavaScript, providing a comprehensive overview of the language's capabilities.
